Problem 1: Softmax MNIST Classification¶

In [4]:
import tensorflow as tf
import keras
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
In [5]:
# Load data set
mnist = tf.keras.datasets.mnist
(x_train, y_train), (x_test, y_test) = mnist.load_data()
In [6]:
# Normalize data
x_train = x_train.reshape(-1, 28 * 28).astype(np.float32) / 255.0
x_test = x_test.reshape(-1, 28 * 28).astype(np.float32) / 255.0
In [4]:
# Shallow network with softmax regression
model_plain = tf.keras.Sequential([
    tf.keras.layers.Dense(10, activation='softmax', input_shape=(28 * 28,))
])
In [5]:
model_plain.compile(optimizer=tf.keras.optimizers.SGD(learning_rate=0.01),
              loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy',
              metrics=['accuracy'])
In [6]:
# Fit model
hist_plain = model_plain.fit(x_train,y_train,epochs=200, validation_data=(x_test, y_test))

Problem 2: Autoencoders¶

Naive Autoencoder¶

In [9]:
# Naive AE with 100 encoder weights
input_img = keras.Input(shape=(784,))
encoded = keras.layers.Dense(100, activation='relu')(input_img)
decoded = keras.layers.Dense(784, activation='sigmoid')(encoded)
autoencoder = keras.Model(input_img, decoded)
In [10]:
autoencoder.compile(optimizer=tf.keras.optimizers.SGD(learning_rate=0.01), loss='binary_crossentropy')
In [11]:
# Fite the model with 150 batch sizes
autoencoder.fit(x_train, x_train,
                epochs=200,
                batch_size = 150,
                shuffle=True,
                validation_data=(x_test, x_test))

Sparse Autoencoder with KL loss¶

In [19]:
# Define the KL loss function
def kl_regularizer(x):
    alpha = 0.1
    lam = 1

    alpha_hat = tf.reduce_mean(x, axis = 0)

    kl_divergence = alpha * tf.math.log(alpha / alpha_hat) + \
        (1 - alpha) * tf.math.log((1 - alpha) / (1 - alpha_hat))

    return lam * tf.reduce_sum(kl_divergence)
In [20]:
# Construct model with normal initialization
init_ae = tf.keras.initializers.RandomNormal(mean=0, stddev=0.1)
input_img = keras.Input(shape=(784,))
encoded = keras.layers.Dense(100, activation='sigmoid', activity_regularizer = kl_regularizer, kernel_initializer = init_ae)(input_img)
decoded = keras.layers.Dense(784, activation='sigmoid')(encoded)
autoencoder_sparse = keras.Model(input_img, decoded)
In [21]:
autoencoder_sparse.compile(optimizer=tf.keras.optimizers.SGD(learning_rate=0.1), loss="binary_crossentropy")
In [22]:
# Fit autoencoder
autoencoder_sparse.fit(x_train, x_train,
                epochs=200,
                batch_size = 64,
                shuffle=True,
                validation_data=(x_test, x_test))

# Use 150 sample sizes to plot hidden unit activation
random_indices = np.random.choice(len(x_train), 150, replace=False)
x_random = x_train[random_indices]
sparse_encoder_weights = autoencoder_sparse.layers[1].get_weights()[0]
hidden_units_activation_sparse = x_random.dot(sparse_encoder_weights)
In [24]:

plt.colorbar()

plt.show()

Problem 3: A shallow NN¶

In [31]:
# Shallow network with softmax regression
model_nn = tf.keras.Sequential([
    tf.keras.layers.Dense(50, activation='relu', input_shape=(784,)),
    tf.keras.layers.Dense(10, activation='softmax')
])

              metrics=['accuracy'])

In [14]:
initializer1 = tf.keras.initializers.RandomNormal(mean=0, stddev=0.01)
model1 = tf.keras.models.Sequential([
          tf.keras.layers.Dense(512,activation='sigmoid',kernel_initializer=initializer1),
          tf.keras.layers.Dense(512,activation='sigmoid'),
          tf.keras.layers.Dense(512,activation='sigmoid'),
          tf.keras.layers.Dense(512,activation='sigmoid'),
          tf.keras.layers.Dense(512,activation='sigmoid'),
          tf.keras.layers.Dense(10,activation='softmax')
 ])
model1.compile(optimizer='sgd',loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy',metrics=['accuracy'])

initializer5 = tf.keras.initializers.HeNormal()
model5 = tf.keras.models.Sequential([
          tf.keras.layers.Dense(512,activation='relu',kernel_initializer=initializer5),
          tf.keras.layers.Dense(512,activation='relu'),
          tf.keras.layers.Dense(512,activation='relu'),
          tf.keras.layers.Dense(512,activation='relu'),
          tf.keras.layers.Dense(512,activation='relu'),
          tf.keras.layers.Dense(10,activation='softmax')
 ])
model5.compile(optimizer='sgd',loss='sparse_categorical_crossentropy',metrics=['accuracy'])
